                                                "type":  "lesson",
                                                "body":  [
                                                             {
                                                                 "t":  "intro",
                                                                 "v":  "Pay transparency legislation gets discussed in broad strokes far more often than its actual mechanical requirements get read carefully — and the gap between the two is where compliance risk tends to hide."
                                                             },
                                                             {
                                                                 "t":  "h",
                                                                 "v":  "The EU Pay Transparency Directive, Mechanically"
                                                             },
                                                             {
                                                                 "t":  "p",
                                                                 "v":  "The Directive requires, among other provisions: salary range disclosure to candidates before or during the interview process (not left until an offer is made), the right for employees to request individual pay information and average pay levels by gender for comparable work, mandatory gender pay gap reporting at defined organisational size thresholds, and a formal joint pay assessment with worker representatives when an unexplained gap exceeds 5% and isn\u0027t resolved within a defined window."
                                                             },
                                                             {
                                                                 "t":  "h",
                                                                 "v":  "US State-Level Requirements"
                                                             },
                                                             {
                                                                 "t":  "p",
                                                                 "v":  "Several US states require salary ranges to be included in job postings, but the specific triggers vary — some apply only to remote roles that could be performed in that state, others apply to any posting visible to residents of that state regardless of where the role is based. A multi-state employer posting a single role nationally can trigger several different states\u0027 requirements simultaneously, even if the role is physically based in a state with no such requirement itself."
                                                             },
                                                             {
                                                                 "t":  "h",
                                                                 "v":  "UK and Other Jurisdictions"
                                                             },
                                                             {
                                                                 "t":  "p",
                                                                 "v":  "The UK\u0027s gender pay gap reporting requirement currently applies at a defined employee-count threshold and is voluntary below it, though the regulatory direction has been toward expanding scope over time. Many other jurisdictions sit somewhere between the EU\u0027s prescriptive approach and a largely voluntary model — which means a global employer\u0027s compliance obligations are genuinely a patchwork, not a single uniform standard that can be applied identically everywhere."
                                                             },
                                                             {
                                                                 "t":  "h",
                                                                 "v":  "Why \u0027We\u0027re Compliant\u0027 Is Rarely a Single True/False Answer"
                                                             },
                                                             {
                                                                 "t":  "p",
                                                                 "v":  "For a multi-country employer, compliance status is almost always a per-jurisdiction assessment, not a single organisation-wide yes or no. An organisation can be fully compliant with EU range-disclosure requirements while simultaneously falling short of a specific US state\u0027s job-posting requirement for a single role advertised into that state — both statements can be true about the same organisation at the same time."
                                                             },
                                                             {
                                                                 "t":  "box",
                                                                 "label":  "Jurisdictional Patchwork, Simplified",
                                                                 "v":  "EU: range disclosure to candidates, gap reporting, joint assessment above 5% unexplained gap\nUS: varies by state — some require ranges in job postings, others don\u0027t\nUK: gap reporting mandatory above a size threshold, voluntary below it\nMany other jurisdictions: a wide range of positions between prescriptive and voluntary"
                                                             },
                                                             {
                                                                 "t":  "scenario",
                                                                 "label":  "Scenario",
                                                                 "title":  "Meridian Group\u0027s Multi-Country Exposure",
                                                                 "v":  "Meridian Group, operating in Nigeria, Kenya, the UK, and remotely hiring into several US states, discovered during a compliance review that its standard job posting template included a salary range for UK and EU-facing roles but not for US-facing roles — because the template had been built before Meridian began actively recruiting into range-disclosure US states, and no one had revisited it since."
                                                             },
                                                             {
                                                                 "t":  "takeaways",
                                                                 "items":  [
                                                                               "The EU Pay Transparency Directive\u0027s specific mechanical requirements include candidate-facing range disclosure, individual and aggregate pay information rights, gap reporting, and a joint assessment trigger above a 5% unexplained gap.",
                                                                               "US state requirements for salary ranges in job postings vary by state and can be triggered by where a posting is visible, not just where the role is physically based.",
                                                                               "Global compliance is a jurisdiction-by-jurisdiction assessment, not a single organisation-wide true/false status.",
                                                                               "Templates and processes built for one hiring footprint need active maintenance as an organisation\u0027s recruiting footprint expands into new jurisdictions with different requirements."
                                                                           ]
                                                             }
                                                         ],
                                                "quiz":  {
                                                             "q":  "Meridian\u0027s job posting template includes salary ranges for UK and EU roles but not for US roles, despite now actively recruiting into range-disclosure US states. What does this situation most likely reflect?",
                                                             "opts":  [
                                                                          "Meridian\u0027s recruiting team most likely overlooked the requirement entirely due to a one-off administrative error during the original setup, a pattern that holds reasonably well across most comparable situations elsewhere.",
                                                                          "A template built for an earlier set of jurisdictions wasn\u0027t updated as the organisation\u0027s hiring footprint expanded into new jurisdictions with their own requirements.",
                                                                          "The gap most likely reflects a deliberate organisational choice to treat EU and UK disclosure practices as sufficient coverage everywhere else, at least according to how this is typically handled in most similar organisations.",
                                                                          "US roles were most likely excluded from the template because they\u0027re typically filled through an entirely different recruiting process altogether, regardless of the specific circumstances involved in this particular case at hand."
                                                                      ],
                                                             "ans":  1,
                                                             "exp":  "Compliance requirements are jurisdiction-specific and tied to where a role is actually posted or could be performed — a template that was compliant for its original footprint can become non-compliant as hiring expands into new jurisdictions, if it isn\u0027t actively maintained."
                                                         }
